------------------------------------------------------
Create folder "server"
Open terminal inside this folder, then run....

npm init -y 
Creates default package.json

npm install typescript -D 
Install typescript for node

npm install ts-node -D 
Makes node "understand" typescript

npx tsc --init  
Typescript config file

npm install express --save 
Install express

npm install @types/express -D
Install types for IntelliSense

npm ts-node src/server.ts
Run the server

npm install ts-node-dev -D
Run ts-node for developer

npx ts-node-dev src/server.ts
This will "restart" app everytime some file changes

Go to package JSON, under scripts add:
"dev" : "ts-node-dev src/server.ts",

Now its possible to run:
npm run dev 

------------------------------------------------------

Get out serve folder
Create a new folder "web", then run...

npx create-react-app web --template=typescript
Will download react content

------------------------------------------------------

npm i knex
Its a QueryBuilder that will help us making queries to database

------------------------------------------------------

npm i sqlite3
Its a Database

