npm i axios
JSON Request library

------------------------------------------------------

npm i -g expo-cli
Platform to make mobile apps with React

------------------------------------------------------

expo init "name_of_project"
Will create the mobile name

npm start
Will open your browser with a "terminal" for expo
You will be able to scan QR code and use it in Expo Client Android app
You can also use a emular,
Or another webPage as a device

------------------------------------------------------

expo install expo-font @expo-google-fonts/ubuntu @expo-google-fonts/roboto
Install google fonts for reac-native

------------------------------------------------------

npm i @react-navigation/native
Equivalent to "npm i react-router-dom"
Is the router for mobile

------------------------------------------------------

expo install react-native-gesture-handler react-native-reanimated react-native-screens react-native-safe-area-context @react-native-community/masked-view

react-native-gesture-handler: The slide finger detection
react-native-reanimated: Animations
react-native-screens: Handle different screens
react-native-safe-area-context: inhibit touches some place like push notification areas
@react-native-community/masked-view: Didn't understand whats is this, ...

------------------------------------------------------

npm i @react-navigation/stack
Use the "stack" method to navigate between the screen.

------------------------------------------------------

npm i react-native-maps
Allow use maps inside app

